      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Frederik George Pohl (1919-2013) was an American science fiction writer, editor and fan.    He wrote novels and short stories, and was for ten years the editor of the Hugo Award-winning magazines <emph render="italic">Galaxy</emph> and <emph render="italic">If</emph>.  He won numerous awards over the course of his ceventy-five-year career, including the  Damon Knight Memorial Grand Master Award in 1993, and was inducted into the Science Fiction and Fantasy Hall of Fame in 1998.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Robert Alexander Collection Relating to Frederik Pohl</emph> consists of a few items pertaining to science fiction author Frederik Pohl, including two signed items and a photograph of Pohl with an unidentified man.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
